RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 58. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500 (Claiming Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In All owances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HALLIE'S RAINBOW shared the early lead in hand from outside, was two wide through the bend, put to urging upper stretch, steadily opened up on the others and was kept to task to the wire. MISS DUTTON was checked when her path was compromised midway on the backstretch, altered out, progressed two wide on the turn, altered out upper stretch, altered to the inside after entering the last eighth and took over second just inside the seventy yard marker. JAMAICAN TRAFFIC prominent early, was two then three wide taking the bend, gained second upper stretch but slowly wore down in the late going. DELTA LADY was hustled up to vie for the lead from inside but wore down for the drive. UNEEKY altered in looking for a clear path midway on the backstretch, was steadied briefly, moved to the rail shortly after that and soon gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Delta Lady
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent to lead inside, gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Dutton
ENTRY.COMMENT: checked 9/16s, altered path twice stretch, got 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Uneeky
ENTRY.COMMENT: altered in 9/16s, steadied, faded inside

ENTRY.NAME: Hallie's Rainbow
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: much the best, driving

ENTRY.NAME: Jamaican Traffic
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly outside, 2-3 wide turn, weakened late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Special Weight Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PAYNT BY LETTERS soon had the advantage, showed the way just off or along the rail, moved clear when allowed on the second bend and widened command under urging in the lane. EIGHT MAY bumped with VALIENTE CLAYMORE at the break, advanced between rivals to take over second three wide on the second turn, angled in some entering the stretch, was no match for PAYNT BY LETTERS but was unchallenged for the place. DRAGGING MAIN prominent just behind PAYNT BY LETTERS, did not keep up after a half mile, was just off the inside into the lane, angled out deep stretch and caught VALIENTE CLAYMORE for third. VALIENTE CLAYMORE was bumped then squeezed solidly between horses at the start, recovered quickly to prompt the pace, came to the leader on the backstretch, failed to keep up two wide on the second bend and gradually yielded in the stretch. MARCHING ORDERS drifted out some just after the break, bumped solidly with VALIENTE CLAYMORE, moved up to contention from inside on the backstretch but faded after a half mile. DURANGO CHROME was a factor from outside for a half mile then began to yield.

ENTRY.COMMENT: rated inside, let out 2nd turn, urged through stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Eight May
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, 3 wide 1/4, 2 wide stretch, clearly 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WITCHING was kept close between horses, commenced her bid three wide on the bend, took the lead upper stretch, lugged in some inside the last furlong, was engaged from inside, battled on even terms the final sixteenth and edged ahead in time. MINI DRESS in tight quarters between rivals early, gradually moved toward the inside nearing the turn, steadily progressed from inside, caught up with WITCHING in the late going, fought gamely but had to settle for second best. AMARI S. vied for the early lead from inside, moved ahead on the bend, floated out some entering the stretch, began to wear down, angled out some when her path was taken inside the final furlong and was easily best of the others. LORI ATTACK raced in contention toward the outside, retreated some three wide on the turn, fanned out further entering the stretch and had no late bid. WARM BEAUTY chased from along or just off the rail and failed to menace. FILLY FROM ILLY disputed the pace outside AMARI S. on the backstretch but began to yield two wide on the bend. DIAMOND GUCCI showed little in a wide trip.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 67. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLAME TERI rated on the front end from outside, took over when let out some into the bend, moved clear, received mostly hand urging in the lane and maintained full control. LITTLE ACCOUNT without early speed, picked up her pace along the rail on the turn, gained second leaving the bend, came off the rail some for a clear path upper stretch, was no match for BLAME TERI in the late going but lasted for the place. BACKSTAGE BAMBI settled outside, commenced her bid three wide on the turn, fanned out further into the lane, lacked the needed late kick but moved clear for third inside the last eighth. DRAGONFLY KISSES prominent just off the inside, swung out three wide for the stretch and gradually yielded. MIDNIGHT SOCIETY displayed early speed from inside, did not stay with BLAME TERI on the bend, floated out some leaving the turn and gave way for the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 43. Maiden Claiming Purse 8000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIMA ZULU shared the early lead outside LAGRUE, did not stay with that one upper stretch, dug in as he gradually angled out inside the last furlong and got up in time. LAGRUE vied for the lead from just off or along the rail, moved ahead upper stretch, gradually drifted out under left-handed pressure inside the last furlong, was narrowly outfinished but easily best of the rest. UNCLE O. G. pressed the early leaders from just outside, stayed just off the rail taking the bend, raced evenly through the stretch and held onto third. MY KINDA TETON chased from outside, progressed from path three on the turn, fanned out further into the lane and also ran evenly the rest of the way. SPAN chased from just off the inside and had no late bid. THACKER FROMM failed to menace in a ground-saving trip. LORD SHAFTESBURY broke well but soon dropped back, stayed off the inside throughout and showed little.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 80. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 23500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FEVER NATION was soon clear of the rest, rated from inside, asked midstretch then steadily lengthened command under a drive. WILDWOOD RUBEN raced closest to FEVER NATION from the early going, stayed just off the rail taking the bend, was no match for the leader when set down for the drive but was unchallenged for the place. WESLAN hesitated, broke a bit awkwardly, was then steadied briefly behind traffic, just off the inside on the turn, moved to the rail leaving the bend, took over third upper stretch then could only hold his position late. I'M YOUR VALENTINE progressed three wide on the bend then flattened out for the drive. B G ATTACK gave way from inside soon after a quarter mile, was pulled up in the stretch and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 10 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ORBITAL STARR urged along from the early going, came into contention four wide on the bend, was all out in the lane and took over with ninety yards to go. GREAT PLAINES was sent to vie for the lead inside horses, moved ahead as he saved ground through the turn, widened command under urging in the stretch but did not have enough left in the waning yards. STORMIN EL PRADO raced in the second flight from outside on the backstretch, moved clear for third three wide on the bend, lacked a serious stretch bid but pulled away for third inside the last eighth. ARGYBARGY BUCK was prominent from inside early, began to yield into the turn and only passed inside tired ones in the lane. EVIDENCE displayed early speed outside GREAT PLAINES, did not keep up leaving the bend and gave way for the stretch run. I CAN'T TELL YA helped prompt the early pace from between horses but faded two wide on the turn. INDEFENSIBLE hesitated and made a small leap from the gate, was soon well back from the others, picked up his pace some on the bend, angled out widest upper stretch and failed to have a significant response.
